'''A Handful of Time''' (''En H<U+00E5>ndfull Tid'') is a Norwegian film from 1989, directed by [[Martin Asphaug]]. Starring [[Espen Skj<U+00F8>nberg]], Camilla Str<U+00F8>m-Henriksen, Nicolay Lange-Nielsen and [[Bj<U+00F8>rn Sundquist]], the film also features [[Susannah York]] and [[Nigel Hawthorne]]. 

==Plot==
The elderly Martin believes he hears the voice of Anna, the love of his youth who died during childbirth fifty years before. Guided by her voice, Martin escapes from his nursery home and begins a journey that echoes a chain of fatal events from his past, which increasingly merge with the present. 

==Awards==
* Winner of the "Best Film" award at the [[Amanda (award)|Amanda awards]] in 1990.
* Camilla Str<U+00F8>m-Henriksen , winner of the "Best Actress" award at the Amanda awards in 1990.
*The Norwegian entry to the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]] in 1990.
* 1990 Rouen Festival du cin<U+00E9>ma Nordique, Prix A.C.O.R.<ref name=rouen>{{Cite web|last=Rouen Festival du cin<U+00E9>ma Nordique |title=Palmar<U+00E8>s|url=http://www.festival-cinema-nordique.asso.fr/ |language=French}}</ref> 
* 1990 Rouen Festival du cin<U+00E9>ma Nordique, Prix de la presse

